288fdce2-39a5-481e-83af-cbd733476870.label: In London, Ulman was surprised by the non-digital focus of the art school environment, where her net art (developed through early knowledge of coding on platforms like Live Journal) was often undervalued or literally disqualified. This resistance validated her perspective that pervasive internet access had become the inescapable norm, a core concept of Postinternet Art.
